Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with deduction problems and presents a new algorithm to solve a restricted case of higher-order associative-commutative matching. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper mentions an application in the theory of blind signatures. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper deals with translating between natural deduction and sequent calculus. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper presents an algorithm to solve a deduction problem. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper presents an algorithmic approach to solving deduction problems in a specific context.
